title: The Mind Benders (1963 - UK) [Dirk Bogarde] thriller
description:
The Mind Benders (1963 - UK)

Drama / Thriller

starring . . . . Dirk Bogarde, Mary Ure, John Clements
 
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0057311/


Filmed at Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, UK

The film opens with an elderly scientist committing suicide by jumping off of a moving train. Next to his body is found a suitcase filled with cash, apparently the money he was given for leaking top-secret scientific information to the Communists. What seems like a simple open and shut case of treason is actually much, much more complicated. The scientist was working on a disturbing project called Isolation in which he was attempting to find out what happens to the human brain when all of the senses are taken away.
